# Styling Rules

## Token Usage

### Spacing, radius, shadows — SCSS variables via `@use`
Import the token file and use the SCSS variable directly.

| Token file | Variables |
|---|---|
| `@/styles/tokens/spacing` | `$spacing-*` |
| `@/styles/tokens/radius` | `$radius-*` |
| `@/styles/tokens/shadows` | `$shadow-*` |

```scss
// ✅
@use '@/styles/tokens/spacing' as *;
@use '@/styles/tokens/radius' as *;
padding: $spacing-4;
border-radius: $radius-md;

// ❌
padding: 16px;
border-radius: 6px;
```

### Typography — CSS `font` shorthand via `var(--font-*)`
Typography is consumed through **font shorthand custom properties** defined in `src/styles/theme/typography.scss`. Each variable encodes `font-weight`, `font-size`, `line-height`, and `font-family` in a single declaration. **Never** import `@/styles/tokens/typography` in component files.

```scss
// ✅ — one declaration covers size, weight, line-height, and family
font: var(--font-label);

// ✅ — letter-spacing is NOT part of the font shorthand; always set it separately
font: var(--font-label);
letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-snug);

// ✅ — weight-only override (e.g. a selected-state modifier) stays as font-weight
font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);

// ❌ — do not set font-size, font-weight, or line-height individually
font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
line-height: var(--line-height-normal);

// ❌ — do not import the SCSS token file in components
@use '@/styles/tokens/typography' as *;
font-size: $font-size-sm;
```

Available font shorthand presets (`weight size/line-height family`):

| Variable | Value | Typical use |
|---|---|---|
| `--font-caption` | 400 0.75rem/1.5 | Helper text, error messages, captions |
| `--font-sm` | 400 0.875rem/1.5 | Small body text, checkbox labels |
| `--font-sm-relaxed` | 400 0.875rem/1.625 | Accordion content, relaxed small text |
| `--font-base` | 400 1rem/1.5 | Body content, select trigger |
| `--font-lg-relaxed` | 400 1.125rem/1.625 | Descriptions, introductory copy |
| `--font-label` | 500 0.875rem/1.5 | Form labels |
| `--font-control` | 500 0.875rem/1.25 | Buttons (sm/md), accordion triggers |
| `--font-control-lg` | 500 1rem/1.25 | Large buttons |
| `--font-strong-sm` | 600 0.875rem/1.25 | Toast titles, step indicators |
| `--font-title` | 600 1.125rem/1.25 | Modal titles, section headings |

Individual override properties (for single-property changes only):

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `--font-weight-medium` | `500` |
| `--font-weight-bold` | `700` |

Letter spacing (always set separately — not part of `font` shorthand):

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `--letter-spacing-tight` · `snug` · `normal` · `wide` · `wider` · `widest` | `-0.02em` → `0.1em` |

### Colors — CSS custom properties via `var(--*)`
Use CSS custom properties for anything that changes between light and dark themes.

```scss
// ✅ — adapts to theme automatically
color: var(--color-text);
background: var(--color-surface);
border-color: var(--color-border);

// ❌ — hardcoded, breaks dark mode
color: #111827;
```

Available color custom properties are defined in `src/styles/theme/light.scss` and `dark.scss`.

## BEM
Follow BEM strictly for all module class names. Always nest elements and modifiers inside the root block class using the `&` prefix — never write them as flat sibling rules.

```scss
// ✅ — nested from the first layer
.card {
  // block base styles

  &--featured { }          // block modifier

  &__header {              // element
    &--sticky { }          // element modifier
  }

  &__body { }
}

// ❌ — flat rules, breaks the nesting convention
.card { }
.card--featured { }
.card__header { }
.card__header--sticky { }
```

Keep nesting to a maximum of 3 levels (block → element → state/modifier). Pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements (`:hover`, `:focus-visible`, `::before`) count as the innermost level.

## Transitions
- Always list individual properties — **never `transition: all`**
- Use short durations for micro-interactions (100–200ms), slightly longer for layout (250–350ms)

```scss
// ✅
transition: background-color 150ms ease, color 150ms ease, box-shadow 150ms ease;

// ❌
transition: all 200ms ease;
```

## Selectors
- Keep nesting shallow (max 3 levels)
- Scope interactive states (`:hover`, `:focus-visible`) inside the base class block
- Gate `:hover` and `:active` with `:not(:disabled)` for accessible interactive elements
